greeting: Greetings from The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences! http://oeis.org/

results.name: Array read by antidiagonals giving number of paths up and left from (0,0) to (n,k) where x/y<n/k (except at start and finish).
formula: Some identities: a(n, k)=a(k, n); a(n, m*n)=a(n, m*n-1); a(n, n)=A000108(n-1); if n and k are coprime then a(n, k)=A071201(n, k)
results.author: _Henry Bottomley_, May 16 2002
